@page "/layout/grid"
<MainContentHeader Title="Grid system">
    <Description>Use our powerful mobile-first flexbox grid to build layouts of all shapes and sizes thanks to a twelve column system, five default responsive tiers, Sass variables and mixins, and dozens of predefined classes.</Description>
</MainContentHeader>

<PageSection Id="howitwork" Title="How it work">
    <Paragraph>
        Bootstrap’s grid system uses a series of containers, rows, and columns to layout and align content. It’s built with flexbox and is fully responsive. Below is an example and an in-depth look at how the grid comes together.
    </Paragraph>
    <Example Code="&lt;Container&gt;
                &lt;GridRow&gt;
                    &lt;GridColumn SmallWidth=&quot;GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance&quot;&gt;One of three columns&lt;/GridColumn&gt;
                    &lt;GridColumn SmallWidth=&quot;GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance&quot;&gt;One of three columns&lt;/GridColumn&gt;
                    &lt;GridColumn SmallWidth=&quot;GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance&quot;&gt;One of three columns&lt;/GridColumn&gt;
                &lt;/GridRow&gt;
            &lt;/Container&gt;">
        <Content>
            <Container>
                <GridRow>
                    <GridColumn SmallWidth="GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance">One of three columns</GridColumn>
                    <GridColumn SmallWidth="GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance">One of three columns</GridColumn>
                    <GridColumn SmallWidth="GridColumnDefaultWidth.Instance">One of three columns</GridColumn>
                </GridRow>
            </Container>
        </Content>
    </Example>
</PageSection>
